                  The Wharton School is the business school of the University of Pennsylvania, an Ivy League university in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. Wharton was the world’s first collegiate business school and the first business school in the United States. It was established in 1881 through a donation of Joseph Wharton.                





 Career History



Founder

                                    2005 - Current                


Candlewood Investment Group LP


                  Candlewood Investment Group's investment strategies include, but are not limited to, distressed debt, event-driven, value equity, relative value, capital structure arbitrage, convertible arbitrage, credit, current income and structured credit strategies. These strategies involve various liquidity profiles, such as liquidity upon realization events, while other strategies offer semi-annual, quarterly or daily liquidity. Candlewood may invest in securities and obligations denominated in foreign currencies and/or traded outside the US. They may also employ the use of leverage. They use leverage in their structured credit investment strategy for certain Candlewood Funds. may also leverage the investment return of their clients with options, short sales, swaps, forwards and other derivative instruments.                




Managing Director

                                    2003 - Prior                


Credit Suisse First Boston USA, Inc.


                  Credit Suisse First Boston USA, Inc. provides investment banking services. It offers securities underwriting, trading, mergers, acquisitions advice, research, private equity investment, derivative and risk management products. The company's services include private banking and asset management. Credit Suisse First Boston USA is headquartered in New York, NY                




Banking Analyst

                                    1997 - 2000                


Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette International


                  Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette or DLJ is a defunct U.S. investment bank founded by William H. Donaldson, Richard Jenrette and Dan Lufkin in 1959. Its businesses included securities underwriting; sales and trading; investment and merchant banking; financial advisory services; investment research; venture capital; correspondent brokerage services; online, interactive brokerage services; and asset management.

In August 2000, DLJ (which was majority owned by AXA Financial) announced that it was being bought by Credit Suisse. The firm was headquartered at 277 Park Avenue in New York City and employed 11,300 people as of July 2000.                




Professional

                                    Prior                


Credit Suisse Group AG


                  Credit Suisse Group AG operates as a financial services company, which provides investment banking and advisory services. It operates through six segments: Swiss Universal Bank, International Wealth Management, Asia Pacific, Global Markets, Investment Banking & Capital Markets and Strategic Resolution Unit. The Swiss Universal Bank segment offers advice and a wide range of financial solutions to private, corporate and institutional clients primarily domiciled in the Group's home market Switzerland. The International Wealth Management division provides private banking financial solutions to wealthy private clients and external asset managers in Europe, Middle East and Africa and Latin America. The Asia Pacific division offers integrated private banking and investment banking financial solutions to wealthy individuals, institutional investors and corporate clients in the Asia Pacific region, empowered with the tools of the Group's global resources. The Global Markets division includes a broad range of equities and fixed income products and services and focuses on client driven businesses and supporting the Group's private banking and wealth management businesses and its clients. The Investment Banking & Capital Markets division offers a broad range of investment banking services to corporations, financial institutions, financial sponsors and UHNWI and sovereign clients. The Strategic Resolution Unit was created to facilitate the immediate right sizing of the business divisions from a capital perspective and includes remaining portfolios from the former non-strategic units plus transfers of additional exposures from the business divisions. The company was founded by Alfred Escher on July 5, 1856 and is headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.                




Professional

                                    Prior                


Credit Suisse First Boston LLC


                  Credit Suisse First Boston LLC provides global investment banking services in the United States. It provides private banking and financial advisory services and banking products. Its businesses include securities underwriting, sales & trading, investment banking, private equity, alternative assets, financial advisory services, investment research and asset management. It is headquartered in New York, NY.                




